    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, thanks. i also read that they can get blocked up sometimes, like by bugs or ice. what happens to the airspeed reading if the tube gets clogged?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the pitot tube gets clogged, the airspeed reading will become dangerously inaccurate, which is a real hazard. When the tube is blocked, it can't properly capture the dynamic pressure—the pressure created by the air rushing over the aircraft. Instead of measuring the difference between the moving air pressure and the static pressure, the system essentially just reads the static pressure, or sometimes it reads very low or erratic readings. This means the pilot loses the true indication of how fast they are moving, which is a serious problem, especially if they are trying to maintain a safe speed.",
      "source": "target",
