      "role": "user",
      "content": "right. so if it's iced up or something, it's basically just giving the pilot false info. is there any way to tell if the reading is wrong vs the plane actually slowing down? like how do they verify it's actually the tube that's the problem?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
